alf, there are weapons like the frostbringer that you dont sacrafice very much damage to get the taunt. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7023  target="web">smushums<a</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ualdarionshard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aldarion Shard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/14/02 4:30:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3559.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: best non-proc buyable agro setup?</span><hr size=1> darkess, what you said makes next to no sense.  care to expand?<br><br>54 warrior.  why exactly would i NOT want agro when im MT? <p><i>No, really, magic pajamas were always intended to give the wearer greater protection than that of half inch thick steel plate.  really.  whaddaya mean monks are unbalanced? </i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 635<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/14/02 4:46:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3559.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: best non-proc buyable agro setup?</span><hr size=1> Since when is 12/22 a crappy ratio? There are no &quot;cheap&quot; tradeable weapons that will out taunt a Frosty even if you never proc. If you want tradeable weapons that have a good enough ratio and are fast enough to generate good agro, they you are going to spend a lot of plats.<br><br>As a matter of fact, I can think of 2 weapons that are that good:<br><br>Horn of Hsagra<br>Swiftblade of Zek<br><br>If you consider weapons that are tradeable, have a great ratio, and a proc that may or may not be good agro then you have:<br><br>Fleshgrinder<br>Frostbringer<br>Guard Capt's Mallet<br><br>Any weapons that have worse ratios than these weapons are going to taunt like a wet noodle. You basically have 2 choices when it comes to tradeable weapons 1) spend a fortune on super ratio weapons or 2) spend a sizable chunk on decent ratio + proc weapons. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial"><img src="http://www.bfdesigns.net/eq/wandor_sig.jpg"><br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor's profile</b></a> | <a target="_blank" href="http://www.exarch.net/"><b>Fusion of Flame</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102" target="_blank"><b>Moordian's profile</b></a></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usmushums.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smushums</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 1175<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/14/02 5:14:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3559.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: best non-proc buyable agro setup?</span><hr size=1> it took me a couple levels to get a frostbringer cuz i always found some armor piece i wanted more... they were expensive back then.  now, one expansion later, i still havent found a tradeable weapon as good as frostbringer for agro.  as a matter of fact, ev hammer is the best ratio i've found for an offhand weapon with any reasonable price...  and its only 2dly better.<br><br>i try to keep two sets of weapons, one taunt and one non-taunt.  i desperately need a main hand taunt weapon, but epic has offhand covered pretty good.  i didnt really put out enough damage to taunt using non-proc weapon in pickup groups until i got primal...  and even then i still had problems with some people stealing agro.<br><br>sorry if my earlier post was a bit harsh, i was still a bit ticked after reading what some retard posted on another thread. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7023  target="web">smushums<a</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubouldor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bouldor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/14/02 5:49:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3559.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: best non-proc buyable agro setup?</span><hr size=1> Non-proc weapons just don't cut it for aggro.<br><br>Your logic does not make a lot of sense to me. You say that procs are too unreliable. In response, you decide to go with weapons that have ZERO chance to proc. <br><br>I have gotten decent aggro using high damage 2h weapons with a ratio better that 1/1 dmg/delay.<br><br>I would guess your best buyable non-proccer will be Swiftblade of Zek or Horn of Hsagra. You might also consider the Stonebladed Axe of Dismay. I believe it is 44/44. That MAY be decent aggro, but probably not.<br><br>Procs are the best way to hold aggro, reliability or not.<br><br> <p><img src="http://www.enjoyer.com/barrel.gif" width="270" height="150" border="0">