pic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gs.cdnow.com/graphics/COVERART/local/L/80/01/00138001.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: best non-proc buyable agro setup?</span><hr size=1> If you have very good dps weapons then you won't need procs to get aggro.  Example: SBoZ<br><br>You shouldn't be relying on procs for aggro.<br><br>You can't go with one of these choices, you have to find a happy medium.  At least one of your weapons needs to have a proc.  If you have good dps then you can get two weapons with procs.<br><br>Don't sacrifice dps just for procs, and vice versa.  Go to CT with non procing weapons and try to play the dps game with a monk or rogue in a_uber_guild00.  You won't win.  <br><br>Back in the day I spent 25k on a Frostbringer and it was worth it.  I used it for a year.  Now it is about 7k and worth every penny.  12/22 is not a shabby ratio.  Get it.<br><br>For offhand you can do Guard Mallet, or get a group and kill General.   <p><b>Lochraven<b><br>Warlord<br>The Nameless</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukilaara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kilaara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/14/02 11:47:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3559.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.elchtom.de/Fantasy/f49.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: best non-proc buyable agro setup?</span><hr size=1> Yesterday I had to use a journeyman walking stick 9/24 for the tashani proc, cause we lacked a chanter.<br><br>Was a 