udget, but just get a Frosty.  Im almost def positive that if you and a warr were to try to tank a mob, the one with the frosty will win.  Say you had two lamentations, and I had a lammy and frostbringer.  I will 10 times outta 10 steal the aggro of the mob.  <br><br>Just accept it, procs are the way to go.  Im not saying its not possible to hold agro with damage weapons only, but the way EQ goes its much easier with procs.  If you dont believe me, try it out with a ranger or monk.  They will out ratio you, but because you have procs . . . you can hold aggro. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uscarsoulklaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ScarSoulKlaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 7:12:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3559.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> Look at it this way....<br><br>I was in FG last night in a trio hunting 'shrooms.  Myself (60 warrior with no Archtype skills yet), 59 epic Shaman and a Veteran 60 Ranger.<br><br>The Ranger was armed with a Shadowheart primary and offhand epic, way better base haste than I have, and had really pumped up her Archtype skills.  She also used every weapon buff she had for better DPS.  A challenge for holding agro against to say the least.<br><br>I started the night using my BAH, was able to hold agro for about 30 seconds against this Ranger.  If a 'shroom landed slow on me it was lost for the duration of the fight.  I tried a few different combinations since this was the first chance I'd had in awhile to check my weapons and tactics for holding agro.  It took me about 10 'shrooms to land a winning combo of 1-handers that we were all satisfied with.<br><br>I changed to FB primary and Spiked Velium Mallet offhand.  Even when hit with the slow I was able to hold the agro 80% of the time via the proc.  The extra stats and damage from the SVM were a great compliment to the FB.  DPS was solid, and the 'shrooms, lotus and Dregs were falling like rain.<br><br>I think we stopped 2 times in 3.5 hours for med breaks, neither of which went longer than 3 minutes.  Since I was taking most of the damage again I could use my BP for heals and save the group downtime between pulls.  If you think we were going slow I got about 1 reg blue and almost an orange of AAXP in that time using an 80/20 split favoring AAXP.  My lifebar never dropped below half the whole time.<br><br>At the end of the night I was quite satisfied that I had a combo of weapons that would hold up for the time being.  I would group with this Ranger anytime now without being worried about how things were going to work out.  I'm looking forward to the next time we hunt together when I should have my haste upgrade (finally !!)<br><br>Morale of the story?  Get the FB - you won't be disappointed with it.<br><br>Good Hunting.... <p>Scartle SoulKlaw<br>Dwarven Warlord of E'CI<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69785">The game has been good to me...</a> </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uscarsoulklaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ScarSoulKlaw</A> at: 8/15/02 7:13:47 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uskyyzulsquinteye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skyyzul Squinteye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 7:33:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3559.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> My guild's MA uses a ToD/Frosty combo, dragon haste, tons of AAs, etc. Even if I give her a good 30sec head start on mobs like Vindi, I constantly get slapped and have to back off. What am I swinging? Stonebladed Axe of Dismay. No taunting, no slamming, no kicking, no disarming. I died on our last Vindi kill when I got aggro, backed off at about two bubbles of health, waited outside of fight for about 30 secs hoping for a heal or two - MA got stunned, and I got summoned and dropped. Oh, and my haste is a crappy SBoC. If you want taunt without a procc'ing weapon, do not discount high-ratio two-handers. Oh, and I was MA for Va'Dyn with this same axe, and had no problem keeping aggro. Fact is, I don't have any one-handers I can count on to keep aggro as well as this axe, so I don't bother switching weapons anymore. Been thinking about picking up a Frosty/Wavecrasher combo, since I think it will take at least that to out-taunt my axe.<br><br>One more thing - my axe was 15k. Wavecrasher/Frosty will cost me 65k or so. 'Nuff said. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showMessageRange?topicID=3559.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showMessageRange?topicID=3559.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showMessageRange?topicID=3559.topic&start=61&stop=67>4</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showNextMessage?topicID=3559.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3559.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><